# Cumulative Distribution Function

For a random variable $X$, the function $F$ defined by $$ F(x)=\bbps{X \leq x}, -\infty < x < \infty $$
is called the **cumulative distributive function**, or, more simply, the **distribution function**, of $X$.
Thus, the distribution function specifies, for all real values $x$, the probability that the random
variable is less than or equal to $x$.

