<section class="primary">

# Joint Probability Mass Function

In the case where $X$ and $Y$ are both discrete, we define the **joint probability mass function** of $X$ and $Y$ by
$$ p(x, y) = \bbps{X = x, Y = y}. $$
The probability mass function of $X$ is then found by
$$ p_X(x) = \bbps{X = x} = \sum_{y: p(x, y)> 0} p(x, y), $$
with a similar formula holding for $Y$.

